{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-203-io-kit-device-drivers-for-mac-os-x"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The I\/O Kit is a set of system frameworks and libraries for creating device drivers on Mac OS X, supporting both 32 and 64 bit architectures. Learn about the design of I\/O Kit drivers, as well as tips and tricks for fast, efficient driver development and debugging. Whether you’re bringing a new device to Mac OS X or developing an application to access an existing device, this session is for you."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-203-IO-Kit-Device-Drivers-for-Mac-OS-X","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/203\/"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC10","role":"sampleCode","title":"I\/O Kit Device Drivers for Mac OS X","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Learn More